  "prompt": "What did cavemen eat?",
  "response": "Cavemen, or more accurately, prehistoric humans during the Paleolithic era, had diets that primarily consisted of what they could hunt, gather, and forage. Their diet was varied and largely dependent on their environment and the resources available. Common foods included:\n\n1. **Meat:** Cavemen hunted animals such as mammoths, bison, deer, and smaller game. They consumed the meat, organs, and marrow.\n\n2. **Fish and Seafood:** Those living near water sources had access to fish, shellfish, and other aquatic animals.\n\n3. **Plants:** They gathered edible plants, including fruits, nuts, seeds, leaves, roots, and tubers.\n\n4. **Eggs:** Bird eggs were likely a part of their diet whenever accessible.\n\n5. **Insects:** Insects and other small critters were also a source of nutrition.\n\nThis diet is often referred to as the \"hunter-gatherer\" diet, emphasizing the reliance on natural, unprocessed foods available before the advent of agriculture. The specific foods and proportions varied widely depending on geographic location and the season.",
